SUBSTITUTE FOR
SENATE BILL NO. 530
A bill to amend 1954 PA 116, entitled
"Michigan election law,"
(MCL 168.1 to 168.992) by adding section 482g.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF MICHIGAN ENACT:
1 Sec. 482g. (1) Before the circulator of a petition under
2 section 482 has an individual sign the petition, the circulator
3 must provide both of the following choices to the individual who is
4 signing the petition:
5 (a) Have the circulator indicate to the individual where the
6 summary of the purpose of the proposed amendment or question
7 proposed, as submitted to or as approved by the board of state
8 canvassers, is located on the petition and give that individual the
9 opportunity to read the summary.
STM S00812'25 (S-1) w26tr0

2
1 (b) Have the circulator read to the individual the summary of
2 the purpose of the proposed amendment or question proposed, as
3 submitted to or as approved by the board of state canvassers.
4 (2) If a circulator fails to comply with the requirement under
5 subsection (1) when obtaining a signature on a petition under
6 section 482, the sponsor of that petition is subject to a civil
7 fine of not more than $1,500.00, or $50.00 for each violation,
8 whichever is greater.
